This post is like a reminder for all Android devs who forgot the fact that the Canvas class has a method [drawArc](https://web.archive.org/web/20191022073334/https://developer.android.com/reference/android/graphics/Canvas#drawArc(android.graphics.RectF,%20float,%20float,%20boolean,%20android.graphics.Paint)).

Or you can use a simple library like: [ArcSeekBar](https://web.archive.org/web/20191022073334/https://github.com/MarcinMoskala/ArcSeekBar/). It has smooth animation, you can control the thumb drawable, progress background and color and many more.
